1 PART V. ISSUANCE OF BONDS
2 SECTION 9. General obligation bonds may be issued, as
3 provided by law, to yield the amount that may be necessary to
4 finance projects authorized in part II and listed ih part IV of
5 this Act; provided that the sum total of the general obligation
6 bonds so issued shall not exceed [$12,9-00,0-6-0] $58,300,000."
7 SECTION 3. If any portion of this Act or its application
8 to any person or circumstances is held to be invalid for any
9 reason, the remainder of the Act and any provision thereof shall
10 not be affected. If any portion of a specific appropriation is
11 held to be invalid for any reason, the remaining portion shall
12 be independent of the invalid portion and shall be expended to
13 fulfill the objective and intent of the appropriation to the
14 extent possible.
15 SECTION 4. If any manifest clerical, typographical, or
16 other mechanical error is found in this Act, the chief justice
17 may correct the error. All changes made pursuant to this
18 section shall be reported to the legislature at its next regular
19 session.
20 SECTION 5. Statutory material to be repealed is bracketed
21 and stricken. New statutory material is underscored.
